RECIPE OUTPUTS / FINDS

This file controls the item icons displayed underneath a recipe entry in the Field Guide.

Example:

{
"additions": [
{
"entry": "fieldguideadditions:crafting_table_recipe",
"value": "minecraft:crafting_table"
}
]
}

FIELD EXPLANATIONS

"entry"

The Field Guide entry ID that the item should be added to.

Example:

fieldguideadditions:crafting_table_recipe

IMPORTANT

This ID must match the recipe entry ID used in:

examples/example_datapack/data/fieldguideadditions/fieldguide/categories/recipes.json

It should also match the recipe mapping file and lang keys.

"value"

The item that will be displayed underneath the recipe grid.

Example:

minecraft:crafting_table

FULL EXAMPLE

{
"entry": "fieldguideadditions:crafting_table_recipe",
"value": "minecraft:crafting_table"
}

This displays the Crafting Table item underneath the recipe entry:

fieldguideadditions:crafting_table_recipe

REMEMBER

The entry ID must match everywhere:

Category Entry:
fieldguideadditions:crafting_table_recipe

Recipe Mapping:
fieldguideadditions:crafting_table_recipe

Recipe Output / Find:
fieldguideadditions:crafting_table_recipe

Lang Name:
fieldguide.name.fieldguideadditions.crafting_table_recipe

Lang Description:
fieldguide.fieldguideadditions.crafting_table_recipe.description

If the IDs do not match exactly, the item may not appear under the recipe grid.
